Defendant Derrick D Poindexter in court with attorney Andrew R Rider.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant entered a plea of guilty to the charge. Court conducted plea colloquy with defendant. Court found defendant guilty. 
Victim provided statement to the court. 

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS STRAIGHT TIME; after 40 days, the balance may be served with HUBER, w/Standard Release Conditions (CREDIT - 5 days if revoked); CONCURRENT TO 15CM313;

TERM OF PROBATION:  14 MONTHS;
  
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;   
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No violent contact with the victim. 
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State certified batterers intervention program and/or Anger Management Counseling.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (Court waived DV surcharge), apply balance of cash bail from 15CM1000; remaining balance to be paid as a condition of probation;

Court waives the DNA Surcharge based on date of violation.
